Pair this with definitions of the external modules:

```verilog
module Source(output source);
  assign source = 1'b0;
endmodule

module Sink(input sink);
  initial begin
    $display("start");
    #10;
    $display("sink: %d\n", sink);
  end
endmodule

module AltSource(input source);
  assign source = 1'b1;
endmodule
```

This should print "sink: 0" but prints "sink: 1".

Dropping the instance named `Test` in `Mid` restores the intended behavior.

If/when we supported preserving bundles as structs, this could also occur with a struct named "Test".

While lint tools would be grumpy with these names, we really should never be emitting incorrect Verilog.
